            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "An option is to add `ui_flush()` unconditionally to `vim.wait()` just as recently was done for #25927.\r\n\r\nAdding a flag in the message is the wrong way to go IMO. **All** messages are intended to be actually displayed. What we need is to find blocking waits which override normal event processing/redrawing and add `ui_flush()` in those places.",
